This paper is about improving machine translation using neural networks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also utilizes LSTM recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in deep learning and machine learning research, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper involves alignment and prediction, which are common topics in neural networks and optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves language modeling and translation modeling, which could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it involves analyzing and processing language data.
